David Kortini's body was found dangling from a tree at Maisha Kamili in Pokot Central. [Courtesy]  A family suffered double tragedy after a man was found dead under unclear circumstances shortly after his brother passed on.  West Pokot County Police Commander Jackson Tumwet said the body of David Kortini, 39, was found dangling from a tree at Maisha Kamili in Pokot Central Sub-county.  "According to neighbours, Kortini was seen the previous night in a depressed mood after his brother passed on following a short illness," he said.  He said the body was moved to Kapenguria County Referral Hospital.  Woman who accidentally killed son to know her fate next month  Police yet to arrest suspect who killed woman, hid her body  Woman arrested over death of Nakuru policeman  Two more people shot dead in Kerio Valley, days after CS Matiang’i's visit In another incident, a motorbike rider died on the spot after being involved in a road accident along Kitale-Lodwar highway at Sebit yesterday morning.  Mr Tumwet said the driver of the motor vehicle was from Kapenguria heading towards Lodwar when he collided head-on with the rider.  The body was taken to Kapenguria County Referral Hospital.   Pokot South sub-county has banned the sale & consumption of alcohol for the last 45 years  Mwaka jana zaidi ya watu Hamsini waliuawa kinyama katika eneo la Nadome kutokana na vita baina ya ja  Leaders call for peace among residents living along borders of Baringo, Elgeyo Marakwet and Pokot By Nikko Tanui | 4 hours ago By Anne Atieno | 4 hours ago By Brian Kisanji | 6 hours ago By Fidelis Kabunyi | 20 hours ago